tldr: The user wanted to add a database and an admin dashboard to a sleep
  questionnaire application. The plan involved updating demographics, creating a
  Prisma schema, implementing API routes, setting up simple password
  authentication, and building an admin dashboard. The implementation was
  completed, and the authentication was later simplified using Next.js
  middleware.
overview: The user aimed to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  integrating a database for storing responses and developing an admin dashboard
  for client data access. The chosen approach involved using NeonDB (PostgreSQL)
  with Prisma for efficient data management. Key decisions included refining the
  demographic data structure to align with the SOW and implementing a
  straightforward password-based authentication for the admin dashboard.
  Initially, a custom session management system was developed, but it was
  subsequently simplified by leveraging Next.js middleware for more efficient
  and cleaner route protection. The final outcome is a robust system capable of
  capturing questionnaire responses, securely storing them, and providing an
  authenticated interface for viewing and exporting data in CSV format.
